&lt;p&gt;SharkNinja&amp;nbsp;is a global product design and technology company, with a diversified portfolio of 5-star rated lifestyle solutions that positively&amp;nbsp;impact&amp;nbsp;people’s lives in homes around the world. &lt;strong&gt;Powered by two trusted, global brands, Shark and Ninja&lt;/strong&gt;, the company has a proven&amp;nbsp;track record&amp;nbsp;of bringing disruptive innovation to market and developing one consumer product after another has allowed&amp;nbsp;SharkNinja&amp;nbsp;to enter multiple product categories, driving significant growth and market share gains. Headquartered in Needham, Massachusetts with more than&amp;nbsp;4,100&amp;nbsp;associates, the company’s products are sold at key retailers, online and offline, and through distributors around the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI at SharkNinja &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At SharkNinja, we’re building an AI-native culture. We’re not waiting for the future; we’re creating it. Our people are expected to experiment boldly, adopt new tools, and continuously raise what’s possible to create meaningful impact for our consumers. If you believe the best way to do your job hasn’t been invented yet, you’ll fit right in.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Associate Creative Director of Art to help define what Ninja looks like next. This is a role for a conceptual leader with a solid branding background and a passion for bringing new brands and products to life — someone who collaborates closely with their writing partner to generate breakthrough creative ideas that sell products across Packaging, In-Store, OTT, Social, Experiential, DTC, and Amazon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are imaginative and prolific, not precious, about your ideas. You can take a brief and realize it through fresh, disruptive executions. You are super detail-oriented, ultra-collaborative, and can handle the grind of iterating until we find the breakthrough story. You think in systems, not just assets — building platforms and identities that scale across every touchpoint and perform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have at least 8 years of creative agency or in-house experience, with a thorough understanding of product marketing. Start-up experience is a plus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the creative strategy for new product launches across Ninja brands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define product identities from the ground up in partnership with product and insights teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring new products to market via creative storytelling including naming, logo executions, and visual identity/design language&lt;/li&gt;
